# Battle Engine Rules

## Multiplayer

- Turn resolution is **server-side only** (`battle-resolution.ts`, `/api/battles/[id]/submit`)
- Never add client-side turn execution for RTDB battles
- Use seeded RNG (`battle-rng.ts`) — do not use `Math.random()` for MP battle outcomes

## Shared engine

- Offline and multiplayer share `team-battle-engine.ts` — changes affect both modes
- After engine edits: `npm run test:unit` + `npm run test:integration`

## UI parity

- Battle log display: use `battleLogToDisplayLines()` in both `RTDBBattleComponent` and `OfflineBattleComponent`

## Hydration

- Pokémon slots may lack full stats/moves — hydrate via `getPokemon()` before engine runs
- See `hydrateSlot()` in `useOfflineBattleState.ts` and `battle-resolution.ts`
